article.headline: Duquesne 76, MD Baltimore Co 69
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Bryant McAllister scored a career-high 30 points to lead Duquesne to a 76-69 win over the University of Maryland, Baltimore County on Saturday, snapping the Dukes' six-game losing streak. McAllister made 14 of 17 free throws for Duquesne (2-7) to become the first Dukes' player to score 30 or more points since Courtney Wallace had 34 on Dec. 12, 2000, against Ohio. The Retrievers (2-5) didn't trail until Kieron Achara made a lay-up with eight seconds to play in the first half to give Duquesne a 33-31 lead. After that, Duquesne never trailed. Achara had 16 points and 11 rebounds for Duquesne, while Martin Osimani added 10. Andrew Feeley had 15 points and 10 rebounds and Rashad Bilal added 14 points for the Retrievers, who trailed by as many as 18 points but pulled within four (71-67) with 1:45 to play. It was the Retrievers' fourth straight road loss.
